Class TestCaseList

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • edu.ncsu.csc216.bbtp.model.TestCaseList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Tabular, java.io.Serializable, java.util.Observer

    public class TestCaseList
extends java.util.Observable
implements Tabular, java.io.Serializable, java.util.Observer
    The TestCaseList class stores TestCases in a LinkedList with various getter methods to retrieve the desired object.
    Author:
    Brian Morris, Nat Ellis

      • addTestCase

        public boolean addTestCase(java.lang.String desc,
                           TestingType type,
                           java.util.Date creation,
                           java.lang.String exp,
                           boolean tested,
                           java.util.Date lastTestDate,
                           java.lang.String act,
                           boolean pass)
        Adds a new TestCase to the list in sorted order by constructing a new TestCase object with the parameters provided, adds this TestCaseList as an observer to the new TestCase, returns true if successful, and notifies the observers of this TestCaseList. If the TestCase cannot be constructed properly, false is returned instead.
        Parameters:
        desc - the description of the new TestCase
        type - the TestingType of the new TestCase
        creation - the creation date of the new TestCase
        exp - the expected results of the new TestCase
        tested - the value of the testing status of the new TestCase
        lastTestDate - the last testing date of the new TestCase
        act - the actual results of the new TestCase
        pass - the boolean that represents whether or not the new TestCase has passed testing
        Returns:
        true if the new TestCase has been added successfully, false otherwise
